$CATEGORY: Morphology/HansenQuinn/Ch4

::Q001::[markdown]nom. pl. of the noun “citizen”:{
	~%-100%ἔλυον#Incorrect. The form for imperfect active indicative 1st sing. of the verb “I loosen” is **ἔλυον** (Ch. 2).
	~%-100%κεκελεύκατε#Incorrect. The form for perfect active indicative 2nd pl. of the verb “I order” is **κεκελεύκατε** (Ch. 3).
	~%100%πολῖται#Correct: **πολῖται** is the correct form for nom. pl. of the noun “citizen” (Chapter 4).
	~%-100%ἀδίκου#Incorrect. The form for masc./fem. gen. sing. of the adjective “unjust” is **ἀδίκου** (Ch. 4).
	~%-100%πέμπω#Incorrect. The form for present active indicative 1st sing. of the verb “I send” is **πέμπω** (Ch. 3).
}


::Q002::[markdown]παιδεύετε:{
	~%-100%aorist (1) active optative 3rd sing. of the verb “I educate”#Incorrect. **παιδεύσειεν** is aorist (1) active optative 3rd sing. of the verb “I educate” (Ch. 3).
	~%-100%nom. sing. of the noun “young man”#Incorrect. **νεανίας** is nom. sing. of the noun “young man” (Ch. 4).
	~%100%present active indicative 2nd pl. of the verb “I educate”#Correct: **παιδεύετε** is future active indicative 2nd pl. of the verb “I educate” (Chapter 2).
	~%-100%aorist (1) active optative 2nd pl. of the verb “I order”#Incorrect. **κελεύσαιτε** is aorist (1) active optative 2nd pl. of the verb “I order” (Ch. 3).
	~%-100%imperfect active indicative 2nd pl. of the verb “I order”#Incorrect. **ἐκελεύετε** is imperfect active indicative 2nd pl. of the verb “I order” (Ch. 2).
}


